 At least six people were killed and three others seriously injured in a horrific head-on collision on the R544. Constable Oris Sabelo Ndlovu (33) along with Elsie Masombuka (28), Minienhle Ndlovu (8), Ntombikayise Ndhovu (6) and Luckia Masombuka (11) were travelling in a Volkswagen Polo sedan when they collided with a Mercedes-Benz sedan. Constable Oris Sabelo Ndlovu Prince Manzi who was in the Mercedes-Benz also lost his life. The three passengers in the Mercedes-Benz were transported to a hospital. Constable Ndlovu was with his two daughters, wife and a relative when the incident occurred on the R544 near Verena at about 20:00. According to the Middelburg Police spokesperson, Captain Khanyisile Zwane, Constable Ndlovu was travelling from Tweefontein to Klarinet as he had to report for duty on Saturday.
The Mpumalanga MEC for Community Safety, Security and Liaison MEC Gabisile Shabalala sent her condolences to the families.     Four killed after minibus and truck collide on N11 near Doornkop Elderly lady escapes with her life Parkrun fever breaks out Military troop imposter arrested • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za